# ZPC — Structured Project Memory

This project uses Zero Point Coder for persistent memory across sessions.

## Core Commands

- `agent-do zpc status` — Check memory state at session start
- `agent-do zpc patterns` — Review conventions before implementing
- `agent-do zpc learn "ctx" "prob" "sol" "takeaway" --tags "t1,t2"` — Capture lesson
- `agent-do zpc decide "problem" --options "a,b" --chosen a --rationale "why"` — Log decision
- `agent-do zpc query --tag X` — Search memory
- `agent-do zpc harvest` — Consolidate lessons into patterns

## When to Capture

- Error resolved → `agent-do zpc learn`
- User correction → `agent-do zpc learn`
- Architecture choice → `agent-do zpc decide`
- Convention discovered → `agent-do zpc learn`

## Before Deciding

Check existing decisions: `agent-do zpc query --type decisions`
Do not re-derive settled decisions.
